HEADWORD: Mirza
<hw>Mir"za</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>m⟦imac⟧rz⟦amac⟧</ets>, abbrev. fr. <ets>m⟦imac⟧rz⟦amac⟧deh</ets>
son of the prince; <ets>m⟦imac⟧r</ets> prince (Ar. <ets>am⟦imac⟧r</ets>,
<ets>em⟦imac⟧r</ets>) + <ets>z⟦amac⟧deh</ets> son.]</ety> <def>The
common title of honor in Persia, prefixed to the surname of an
individual. When appended to the surname, it signifies
<sig>Prince</sig>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mis-</ent>⟦br⟧
